    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00 Revolutions/72: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 1, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your 45, September 28, noon, and 46, September 29, 4 p.m. Could it be
                    maintained that Paez, who is understood to have been Minister of Public Works in
                    the cabinet of ex-President Pons, succeeded <pb facs="0628" n="535"
                        xml:id="pg_535"/> to the presidency in accordance with the provisions of
                    Article 79 of the Constitution of March 26, 1929?<note n="29" xml:id="d546fn29">
                        <hi rend="italic">Constitución Politico, de la República del Ecuador dictada
                            por la Asamblea Nacional Gonstituyente de 1928–29</hi> (Quito, 1929), p.
                        30.</note> Cable your comments.</p>
                <p>Also, advise Department of any specific information relating to the “downright
                    social reforms” which, as reported in your 45, Paez has announced his intention
                    to initiate immediately.</p>
                <p>Have you as yet received any official communication from the Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs of the Paez Government announcing its assumption of power?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
